{"id":34969,"date":"2021-01-17T17:12:02","date_gmt":"2021-01-17T13:12:02","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/?p=34969"},"modified":"2021-07-27T14:19:19","modified_gmt":"2021-07-27T10:19:19","slug":"reward-punishment-grave","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2021\/01\/17\/reward-punishment-grave\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Qubur: Great rewards or punishments in the grave"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Abu Huraira reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201c<strong>Verily, the believer in his grave is within a green meadow. His grave welcomes him with seventy cubits of space and it is illuminated for him like the full moon on a clear night. Do you know why this verse was revealed: He will have a confined life and We will raise him blind on the Day of Resurrection<\/strong> (20:124)? <strong>Do you know what is a confined life<\/strong>?\u201d They said, \u201cAllah and His messenger know best.\u201d The Prophet said, \u201c<strong>It is the punishment of an unbeliever in his grave. By the One in whose hand is my soul, ninety-nine dragons will be given authority over him. Do you know what is a dragon? It is seventy serpents, each serpent with seven heads stinging him and maiming him until the Day of Resurrection.<\/strong>\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Ibn H\u0323ibba\u0304n 3122<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <em>Hasan<\/em> (fair) according to Al-Arna\u2019ut<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a \u0647\u064f\u0631\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0631\u064e\u0629\u064e \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u0650 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0645\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e<s